tweet: To everyone in Northwest Indiana this week, please stay safe, take precautions, and check in on neighbors and loved ones while we deal with this record-breaking cold!  https://www.ready.gov/winter-weather
Please stay safe and keep apprised of any changes to the schedule through our website and social media accounts. 2/2

My Saturday Town Forums are currently scheduled to occur. However, should local public safety officials determine that it is unsafe to travel tomorrow due to inclement winter weather, the Town Forums will be cancelled. 1/2

I am looking forward to discussing your priorities at my 2019 Town Forums that start this Friday at various locations throughout Northwest Indiana. https://www.chicagotribune.com/suburbs/post-tribune/news/ct-ptb-visclosky-town-halls-st-0113-story.html …

It is unacceptable that women earn 67 cents for every dollar that a man earns for the same work in Northwest Indiana. I am proud to cosponsor the Paycheck Fairness Act in the 116th Congress and will continue to support its enactment into federal law. https://thehill.com/hilltv/rising/424126-dem-rep-says-window-of-opportunity-has-opened-for-legislation-benefitting-women …

As the 116th Congress begins, I will continue my efforts to rename the Indiana Dunes National Lakeshore as a national park, so that we may further grow our regional economy and provide our lakeshore with the recognition it deserves. https://www.nwitimes.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/push-for-indiana-dunes-national-park-to-continue-in-new/article_b61bc2e4-0b8d-505b-9967-8fc594ac83fa.html …

I am looking forward to the 2019 Town Forums and hearing directly from residents about their issues of concern and how I can best serve and represent their interests this coming year in the 116th Congress. https://visclosky.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/visclosky-announces-2019-town-forum-schedule …
